  "slug": "sound-machines-integrity-protocol-lower-limb-lecture",
  "title": "SOUND MACHINES — Integrity Protocol / Lower Limb Lecture",
  "summary": "<p>American Artist and Tommy Martinez have produced a new generative interface that remixes a recording of their sound piece <em>Integrity Protocol/Lower Limb Lecture</em> (2023/24). Viewers can explore and create new sonic textures by experimenting with the custom interface. The interface is based on an audiovisual work composed using synthesizers and poetic speech, centering on a disembodied voice — American Artist’s own — that evokes an empty personhood, or the lowest and least counted in society. Text captions scroll against a blue void, suggesting the “blue screen of death” appearing during a system crash.    </p>\n<p>Credits:\nTommy Martinez - Music and Web Programming\nAmerican Artist - Lyrics and Video\nRyan Howe - Recording and Mixing\nKevin Ramsay - Mastering</p>\n",
